==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chancroid
<hw>Chan"croid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Chancre</ets>
+ <ets>-oil</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A venereal sore,
resembling a chancre in its seat and some external characters, but
differing from it in being the starting point of a purely local process
and never of a systemic disease; -- called also <altname>soft
chancre</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>chancroidal</ent>⟦br⟧
